Mensartio ⇔ Mensa? / Min (Egyptian mnw) is an ancient Egyptian god whose cult originated in predynastic times (4th millennium BCE). He was represented in many different forms, but was often represented in male human form, shown with an erect penis which he holds in his left hand and an upheld right arm holding a flail. As KHEM or Min, he was the god of reproduction / as Khnum, he was the creator of all things, "the maker of gods and MEN". / ⇔
